criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  45-64 years of age with at least one risk factor, or ≥65 years of age;

          -  undergoing elective noncardiac same-day surgery under regional or general anaesthesia;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  undergoing surgery under local anaesthesia or surveillance only;

          -  planned duration in the operating room is estimated to be less than 60 minutes;

          -  intervention does not require the presence of an anesthesiologist;

          -  procedure is performed by a nonsurgical specialty (e.g., endoscopy by
             gastroenterology, bronchoscopy by pneumology, radiotherapy or radiology procedures);

          -  intervention is an ophthalmologic procedure;

          -  previously enrolled in the VALIANCE study

          -  patients who do not consent to participate in the study
